metadata.title: Cessna 206
aws::graph::propositions: Cessna 206 Aircraft Variants and Production Details
365 total Cessna 206 aircraft were built in the U206A/TU206A and P206A/TP206A variants.
219 aircraft were built as U206A/TU206A variants.
146 aircraft were built as P206A/TP206A variants.
The U206B Super Skywagon was a 1967 model year Cessna 206 variant.
The U206B Super Skywagon featured minor detail changes from previous models.
The U206B Super Skywagon was powered by a 300 hp (224 kW) Continental IO-520-F engine.
The P206B variant was built as a passenger version.
The TU206B variant was a turbocharged version.
The TP206B variant was a turbocharged passenger version.
The P206B, TU206B, and TP206B variants retained their previous 285 hp (213 kW) IO-520-A and TSIO-520-C engines.
The U206B Super Skywagon was certified on August 3, 1966.
371 total Cessna 206 aircraft were built in the U206B/TU206B and P206B/TP206B variants.
258 aircraft were built as U206B/TU206B variants.
113 aircraft were built as P206B/TP206B variants.
The U206C Super Skywagon was a 1968 model year Cessna 206 variant.
The U206C Super Skywagon featured minor detail changes from previous models.
The U206C Super Skywagon had an increased gross weight of 3,600 lb (1,633 kg).
The P206C variant was built as a passenger version of the U206C.
The TU206C variant was a turbocharged version of the U206C.
The TP206C variant was a turbocharged passenger version of the U206C.
The U206C Super Skywagon was certified on July 20, 1967.

text:
365 total built; 219 (U206A/TU206A), 146 (P206A/TP206A).
U206B Super Skywagon
1967 model year with minor detail changes and powered by a 300 hp (224 kW) Continental IO-520-F engine.  Also built in a passenger P206B and turbocharged TU206B and TP206B variants, all retaining their previous 285 hp (213 kW) IO-520-A and TSIO-520-C engines.  Certified on August 3, 1966.  371 total built; 258 (U206B/TU206B) and 113 (P206B/TP206B).
U206C Super Skywagon
1968 model year with minor detail changes and an increased gross weight of 3,600 lb (1,633 kg).  Also built in passengerP206C and turbocharged TU206C and TP206C variants.  Certified on July 20, 1967.
